aYnAHwKpu7I5JjhYve7ZXTP3pcOuQb98R0Kt0Tqr7zuapMVHKwihuuf5DLO9I4k-XoGa2YuA21ef5uSFoUjSck8wcAq8rdf51lXPcem51LTcQmD2yUFcx0JGVksFK98FGRpleM89LO_zD77IEf87lsvM4XM1pptoGuZZbZOTwb8-DQiPRdTNq9Hj4xV2YdiX74OpnU-c4asJhcppHoBz9oCFAqm9Z4lKzVl5_amgZ_5pqea8OpMmNXezvj8sBVQ5drFt75u5yEpkfBmJvSPv9uGL_Fh421sH9gVEhKWrg-2cBdcBQZux5CiESebfBx7flAoFuZL8Spnvf8LUrEMRRM-swEIO07ehWBPmJQO7UrbHSedT3JwE9qP7Lncxn6EcV7S9Wg53D2Fd1SKmnFc0OP5C-9fA09zn7CWNAJpxn8lEeknP3Bkxacid8Vw6EAdFntnpgo=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating logging configuration**\\n\\nI see that our existing resource configuration only includes JUnit, and we can’t modify the metadata. There’s a risk that the appender plugin discovery might fail if the resource cache isn't included. It seems like the Forge agent will generate metadata externally. It's critical that our tests pass under the native image after this generation, so I need to reset the previous logger context. This might require shutting down and reinitializing, and possibly using a unique context.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_AlwCRW8hZTfYTDQxC0hhChS0|fc_0df45c42b02beb6b016a3e960d31cc819098829d8c25ceed83", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.opentelemetry.instrumentation/opentelemetry-log4j-appender-2.17/2.28.1-alpha/src/test/java/io_opentelemetry_instrumentation/opentelemetry_log4j_appender_2_17/Opentelemetry_log4j_appender_2_17Test.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import io.opentelemetry.sdk.trace.SdkTracerProvider;\nimport java.util.List;", "newText": "import io.opentelemetry.sdk.trace.SdkTracerProvider;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.util.List;"}, {"oldText": "import org.apache.logging.log4j.core.config.Configuration;\nimport org.apache.logging.log4j.core.config.LoggerConfig;", "newText": "import org.apache.logging.log4j.core.config.Configuration;\nimport org.apache.logging.log4j.core.config.Configurator;\nimport org.apache.logging.log4j.core.config.